714998f-a.text:
Vacant lot on the S.E. corner of Fifth Avenue and 107th Street, showing the north side of 107th Streetto Madison Avenue.
May 16, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.

714987f-a.text:
Fifth Ave., east side, south from, but not including East 107th., to and including 106th Streets. Also shown (across clearance), is East 106th Street, south side, east from, but not including Fifth., to and including
Madison Aves.
May 16, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.

718227f-c.text:
(1)
Central Park; Harlem Mere, southern bay; the view is towards Fifth Avenue and 107th Street from Mount St. Vincent. The edifice in the background is the Daughters of Israel building.
May 18, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, seen from the shore; the Daughters of Israel building is in the extreme left background, and the Fifth Avenue Hospital, 105th to 106th Streets, nearer the center.
May 18, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
Harlem Mere, the boathouse and northern shore; the view is east
towards Fifth Avenue.
May 18, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
